 "blurb": "The buffet whisperer. Food, accents, and the unmatchable mock-French of someone who has seen the lobster.",
 "bio": "John Pinette was the great American comic of appetite — the rare comedian who could turn a Chinese buffet into a one-man epic and convince a sold-out theater that this is the deepest material there is. He worked accents and impressions like nobody else (Brando, Gollum, an Ewok, a mock-French waiter), sang inside his bits (Free Willy's 'Will You Be There' got its truest delivery on a comedy stage), and built a body of work entirely around what most comics consider too small to mine: eating, hiking, the price of admission. Pinette toured constantly from the late 1980s until his death in 2014; he was also the carjacking victim in the Seinfeld series finale and played Edna Turnblad in the national Broadway tour of Hairspray.",
